- bug: CTRL-A and check on languagetool.org and you'll see broken images in the
  list of errors. Maybe HTML escaping is missing?

- bug: CTRL-A and check on languagetool.org and you'll get Javascript code checked.
  "Text" in between <script>...</script> should probably be ignored.
  This also happens when checking text files like extension/common/locales/en-US/description.txt.

- if you select a headline and the following paragraph you'll get an error because
  LT doesn't consider the paragraph

- more information for the user in case of a 500 error (check language settings)
